{{doc/start}}
Renders a styled infobox for an in-game item. Data is pulled automatically from [[Module:Data/Items]]. The infobox displays name, description, trade category, creative category, associated building, stack size, weight, flags, and trade prices (buy/sell in Firmarlite Bars).

Pages using this template are auto-generated by <code>foundry_parser generate-pages</code>. Editors can add content below the infobox but should not modify the template call itself.

== Data source ==
Item data comes from [[Module:Data/Items]], which is auto-generated by running:
<pre>foundry_parser generate-lua</pre>
from the game installation at <code>F:\SteamLibrary\SteamApps\common\FOUNDRY</code>. Do not edit data modules directly — all changes will be overwritten on the next generation run.

== Usage ==
<pre>
{{Infobox Item|id=_base_iron_ingot}}
{{Infobox Item|id=_base_iron_ingot|image=Iron Ingot.png}}
</pre>

== Parameters ==
{| class="wikitable"
! Parameter !! Description !! Type !! Status
|-
| <code>id</code> || Item template identifier from the game data (e.g. <code>_base_iron_ingot</code>). || String || Required
|-
| <code>image</code> || Image filename to display in the infobox (e.g. <code>Iron Ingot.png</code>). The module automatically prepends <code>Item_</code>, so this looks up <code>File:Item_Iron Ingot.png</code>. || String || Optional
|}

== Notes ==
* The <code>image</code> parameter should be the bare filename without the <code>Item_</code> prefix — the prefix is added automatically.
* Trade prices are shown in [[Firmarlite Bar (Item)|Firmarlite Bars]] only when the item's <code>can_be_traded</code> flag is set.
* Items with a <code>buildable_object_id</code> link to the corresponding building page using the <code>Name (Building)</code> title form.
* The infobox adds the item to <code><nowiki>[[Category:Items]]</nowiki></code> plus its trade and creative mode categories automatically.
{{doc/end}}
